This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language generation and biases in language models. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to natural language generation. Additionally, it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it analyzes biases towards different demographic groups. Finally, it could belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with sentiment analysis, which is related to the analysis of sound and speech.
